    • Field Detail

      • root

        protected Tree.Node root
        The root of the tree. If there is at least one entry in the tree, then the root is guaranteed not to be null if and only if the sub-classes do not allow null values for their values.

      • equals

        public abstract boolean equals(Object obj)
        Performs a "deep" equality search on the two trees. Checks if both trees have the same number of nodes, and if each node in the tree is equal to one another. Each node in one tree must be a "mirrored" visual placement of another node in the other tree.
        Overrides:
        equals in class Object
        Returns:
        true if the trees are deeply equal; false otherwise.
